Another length delivery to follow. This one is on middle. Pujara stays inside the crease and defends it to the leg side.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Pujara stays back and flicks it to mid-wicket.

EDGY! This was close. On a length, around off. The ball moves away after pitching. Pujara has a poke at it, but with soft hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the man at first slip, but it meets him on a bounce. Pujara needs to settle his nerves and do what he does best, defend.
A length ball, around off. The ball jags in a bit. Pujara looks to flick it away but does not find any good connection on it.
Good length ball, outside off. Pujara shoulders his arms.
Virat Kohli walks out to bat! A lot of pressure on the shoulders of the Indian skipper. His team is actually 0 for 2, can he bail his team out of trouble here?

OUT! CAUGHT! Joe Root's decision of getting Mark Wood early into the attack is paying off really well. Wood serves a short ball and Sharma could not resist himself. This one is down the leg side, Rohit is probably a little early in the pull. It goes more of the toe-end towards deep square leg. Moeen runs in, slides forward and takes a good catch. Wood is on cloud 9, what a spell he is bowling. India in deep trouble now. Rohit is quite disappointed, he is looking at the bottom of his bat as he walks off. Now it is going to be a real test for the Indian middle order. They have not done that great so far and for once, the Indian openers have fallen cheaply in this series.
Commentary.Howout: c Moeen Ali b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: A full-length ball, on off. Sharma was ready for it and pushes it towards mid off.
A sharp bouncer this time. Sharma was tempted to hook it away. But in the end, he smartly ducks under it.

SIX! You cannot bowl to Rohit Sharma, where he likes it the most. A touch short and on off. Sharma rocks back and pulls this over the square leg fence for a maximum. He made that 90 mph look like a slower one. Also, the scores are level now.

Does not time it well! A length ball, around off. The ball come in a bit from outside off. Sharma stays back and punches it through point, but does not find the gap. Haseeb Hameed stops it comfortably.
Good length ball, around off. Sharma stays back and defends it to the off side.
Another good leave! Good length ball, outside off. This one jags in a bit. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms at it.
Good length ball, outside off. This one does not trouble Pujara at all. He leaves it without any hesitation.
Back-of-a-length ball, around off. The ball takes off after hitting the deck. Pujara is surprised by the extra bounce and he defends it late towards gully.
A length ball, around middle. Sharma stays back and flicks it through square leg for just a single this time.
A full length ball, on the pads. Sharma flicks it through mid-wicket. The batters pick up two quiet comfortably.
Anderson serves it on a length, outside off. Sharma shoulders his arms.
Good leave to end a successful over for England! Outside off, comes back in. Not enough though to make the batter play.
Just outside off, Pujara lets it be.
Sharp stuff! Wood is bowling with a lot of fire here! Short and on middle, that is quick! Pujara ducks under it. He is mixing it up really well.
On middle, Pujara defends it onto the ground.
Cheteshwar Pujara walks in at number 3.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Rahul is a goner! Mark Wood gets the wicket England wanted. KL has probably been India's best batter on this tour and he walks back even before the deficit has been erased. Lovely delivery, Wood steams in, goes wide of the crease, lands it on off and then gets it to shape away. Rahul looks to defend but does so inside the line, it kisses the edge and goes into the hands of Buttler. Wood is elated. He is really bowling well and deserved this wicket.
Commentary.Howout: c Jos Buttler b Mark Wood

Commentary.Commentary: A bumper, it is ducked under.
Left on length again, outside off, this one comes back in. Sharma shoulders arms to this one. It goes well over the off pole.
Another one on a length and around off, defended.
A quick run! On off, Rahul pushes it towards cover and takes one.

Really well played in the end! On middle, this one holds its line. Rahul does well to play it with a straight bat. He could have easily tried to work it which could have been an issue but he plays it with a straight bat.
Slightly fuller and on off, Rahul pushes it to mid off.
Just outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Yet again on a length and on middle, Sharma is solid in defense.
Good length and on middle, Sharma plays it to mid on.
Shorter and on off, Rohit pushes it to covers.
Rohit probably misses out at one again! Fuller and on off, Sharma drives but does not beat mid off. That was there to be driven.
Just outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to it.
Fuller this time and on middle, Rohit creams it but to mid on.
Now this one stays a touch low! Another one on a length and just outside off. Rahul looks to defend but is beaten due to the low bounce.
Extra bounce now! Outside off, Rahul lets it be. Buttler collects it around his head.

Review! With 4 seconds on the time Joe Root decides to send it upstairs for a LBW review. The on-field decision is not out. The Ultra Edge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker confirms that it is umpire's call on ball hitting the stumps. England don't lose a reveiw here, but they also don't get the wicket. KL Rahul survives.

NOT OUT! That is clipping the leg pole! Umpire's call it is! England do not lose a review but that was close! This starts around off, it is fuller and comes back in. Rahul for once, plants his front foot way too across, he can't get it his front leg out of the way as he tries to flick. He misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal, Anderson is pleading but turned down. After a chat with Root and Buttler. Root reviews. Replays show that the on-field call will remain. That could have gone eitherway.
Yet another delivery which is not on the stumps. Left alone.
Outside off, the batter does not fiddle with it.
Nicely played in the end! Length and just outside off, Rahul waits and then opens the face of the bat at very end, he guides it past point for two. India trail by only 10.
Back of a length and on middle, Sharma hangs back and defends it onto the ground.
Misses out! Probably looked to hit it way too hard! Shorter and outside off, Sharma looks to slap it but it goes off the underedge to covers.
FOUR! Timed beautifully. Just used the pace of the bowler. Angled into the pads, Sharma flicks, he just puts bat to ball and this races away through mid-wicket.
This time Wood bowls it wide outside off, left alone.
Another bowler who has started a little too straight, on the pads again, Rahul now flicks it towards deep square leg for one.
Full and on the pads, Sharma works it towards deep square leg and takes one.
Mark Wood comes early into the attack. He replaces Ollie Robinson.
On the pads, Rahul looks to flick but it goes off the thigh pad to the keeper. Half an appeal but nothing.
Soft hands! Back of a length and on off, Rahul plays it late and with soft hands, it goes off the outer half towards gully, where the fielder dives to his left and stops it.
BEATEN! Another one on a length, it pitches and moves away. Rahul is beaten as he tries to block.
A bumper now, left alone with ease.
Just outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Really well timed! Fuller and on middle, Sharma shows the face of the bat. He once again just pushes it past the bowler and down to the long off fence. A good over for India.
TWO! Good shot! Fuller and outside off, Rohit pushes it through covers. It is not off the middle and hence, two.
Another one on a length and around off, defended nicely.
Another leave as another one is bowled well outside off.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Blocked.
This time it is a little too wide, left alone. Ollie Robinson has overstepped so it is a no ball.

BEAUTY! Not a lot can be done about that delivery but hope it does not take the edge! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Rohit is beaten as he looks to block. Again we can see the good thing the Indian openers are doing is they are not pushing at the delivery.
Inside edge! Once again on a length and on off, gets it to come back in. Rahul looks to defend but gets an inside edge. An appeal but turned down. England bowlers have started well. Another maiden.
Relentless stuff from Anderson so far! Just continues to bowl that nagging line. On off and on a length. Kept out.

Really well played in the end! Back of a length and on off, this one takes off after landing. Rahul looks to defend but does so by taking a hand off the handle. It hits the higher part of the bat and goes to gully. Good he took that one hand off the handle or it may have gone to the gully fielder for a catch.
A little too wide outside off, left alone.
On a length again and around off, solid from Rahul as he blocks it on the off side.
Good length and it comes back in from outside off, Rahul plays it nice and late to gully.
Now brings it back in but it is well wide outside off. Left alone. A maiden to begin with.
That is a beauty! He was getting it in but this time gets the ball to move away. Length and on off, this one moves away. Rohit is beaten as he tries to block.
On a length and around off, this one comes back in. Sharma looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Another one down the leg side, Sharma looks to flick but misses again.
Right on the money this time! Length and around off, this one holds its line. Sharma looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to point.
Slips this one down the leg side. Rohit looks to flick but misses. Not the best of starts from Ollie.
Who will bowl from the end? It is going to Ollie Robinson.
Really good 4 balls to end! The pitch actually seems a lot lively than yesterday. The last ball is on off, Rahul blocks.
The wicket seems to have quickened up! This is again outside off and it comes back in. Zips through. Rahul plays inside the line and lets it go.
Well left in the end! This one comes back in sharply from outside off, it is a back of a length ball. Rahul does well to take his gloves out of the way and let it go.
Gets his line right this time! Lands it around off and this one comes back in. Stays a touch low. Rahul plays it to covers.
Rohit is underway too! A little too straight once again from Anderson. Sharma works it through square leg and takes one more.
India and Rahul are underway! Anderson probably was looking for some away movement, he starts it on the leg pole but no movement, it is worked through square leg for one.

That's a wrap to the Lord's Test. It was an outstanding game with both teams taking its turn to dominate. India did a bit extra on the final day and that's the reason why they now have 14 points in the ICC World Test Championship. The visitors go top of the table, displacing West Indies who were number one after registering a heart-pumping one-wicket win against Pakistan on Sunday. Right then, that's all we have from this clash. The third Test match will start on 25th August 2021 at Headingley. The first ball will be at 1100 local (1000 GMT) but the build-up will begin much in advance. Cheers!

KL RAHUL IS THE MAN OF THE MATCH! The Indian opener says that it was a proud moment for him and he is happy that his knock helped in a win for India. Adds that they had to give India a good start and his stand with Rohit was very crucial. Mentions that they have been working hard on their skills and even in the first game, the batsmen showed a lot of discipline. Hopes to continue the same in the next three games. On the onfield banter, KL Rahul replies that this is what you expect with two very competitive teams playing and they don't mind a bit of banter. Shares that the bowlers were very pumped after that and wanted to have a go at the English batters.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper, walks up with a big smile on his face. He says that he is super proud of the whole team for the way they stuck to their plans. Adds that the pitch didn't offer much to the bowlers. Further says that the way they played in the second innings was excellent and praises Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Shami. Shares that they had the belief that they can get England all out in 60 overs. On giving Shami and Bumrah a standing ovation at the Lord's Long Room, Kohli replies that it's necessary to applaud what they did and says that it's tough for them for the way they batted. States that both Shami and Bumrah were charged up and brought them the first two wickets at the start as well. Informs that they wanted to improve on their lower order batting and this was one of the focuses and the batting coach has worked hard. Feels that the belief was missing but now they have the desire to do the job for the team. Tells that those were priceless runs and that helped them to win. Mentions that he was a part of the winning team as a player under MS Dhoni last time at Lord's, but this one to get a result in 60 overs is quite special and especially with someone like Mohammed Siraj who was playing his first Test match here. Also shares that what happened in the field really charged them up and gave them the extra motivation. On getting good crowd support, Kohli smiles and says that it was not the same for the first four days but in the second half on Day 5, the crowd got behind them and these things are very crucial. Mentions that the victory came a day later after Independence Day but it's the best gift they can give to the people back home. Signs off by saying that they are not going to sit on their laurels. Regarding how he decides to take the DRS, Kohli answers that he likes to go with his instincts and he is ready to take the blame. Feels that if you don't take a chance, you will never know.

Joe Root, the English skipper, says that it's unfortunate that they didn't manage to see off 60 overs which is frustrating. Adds that the batters will be coming hard in the next three games. Root takes the blame and says that a lot depended on him and tactically he could have done better as a captain this morning. Mentions that he has to do a lot of learning and make sure to improve and be ready when next time a similar situation arrives. Further says that they didn't get many things wrong and only a few things went slightly wrong. Tells that Mark Wood and Moeen Ali played brilliantly, the former hurt himself but still showed the attitude to compete. Adds that it's good to have Moeen back and nice to see him enjoy his game. States that they are used to playing 5-match series and they have been in this situation before and have found a way to bounce back. Praises the crowd for their attendance and says that it's good to have the crowd back.
Stay tuned for the presentation...

As mentioned earlier, the momentum refused to stay in one corner in this Test match. Day 5 was no different. Once England removed the dangerous Rishabh Pant, they would have felt the Test was theirs for the taking. But, Shami and Bumrah, emerged as unlikely heroes with the bat and helped India to a position from where the fear of losing the Test match went out of their minds. After setting a target of 272 runs in 60 overs, the Indian bowlers turned on the heat and grabbed the series lead.

The penultimate day of this Test match turned out to be too tough for India as they lost three star batters in the morning session. With two out-of-form batsmen in the middle, we all hoped England to remove them quickly but this Test match never went in a straight line. Cheteshwar Pujara and Ajinkya Rahane formed a century stand to lead the recovery. India started to claw their way back but just when it appeared that they will run away with a handy lead on Day 4, the English bowlers again made a comeback to get rid of both of them and Ravindra Jadeja.

The picture changed on Day 2. England bounced back with renewed energy and once again James Anderson was the centre of attraction. He led the charge with a 5-wicket haul and halted India's dominance. The touring team wasted a golden chance to bat England out of the match after losing 7 wickets for only 88 runs. The 'moving day' started with England's purposeful batting and Joe Root led them from the front. Two able partners in Jonny Bairstow and Moeen Ali rallied around Joe for vital partnerships and England looked set to out-bat India. But as was the case, momentum wasn't anyone's friend in this Test. The Indian bowlers seized the initiative in the final session of Day 3 and picked five wickets in a hurry to strand Joe Root (180) and restrict England's lead to only 27 runs.

England versus India, clash of the Titans! This Test series saw a massive build-up but the first Test turned out to be a damp squib mainly due to the weather. But if anyone had any doubt about the magnitude of this clash between two powerhouses of cricket, it was put to rest in the Lord's Test. We were a witness to some intense battle and captivating cricket. India got challenging conditions to bat in their first innings but the way Rohit Sharma and KL Rahul weathered the storm was simply amazing. Their opening partnership blunted England's bowling plans and another century stand between Rahul and Virat Kohli made Joe Root regret his defensive decision to bowl first on Day 1.

What a cracking finish to this outstanding Test match! Both teams fought tooth and nail and towards the end, it's India who have prevailed. England will be deeply disappointed with their batting, they had 60 overs to negotiate but the top batsmen flopped miserably. Credit to Jos Buttler though who batted against his natural instinct and consumed 96 balls during his stay. He was involved in a couple of stands with Moeen Ali and Ollie Robinson to keep England in the hunt but India managed to find a way to break those partnerships and register a big win. All their pacers were incredible but Mohammed Siraj impressed the most with his lively spells and knack of picking wickets.

The Indian players are running in celebration! Virat Kohli is pumped up. Siraj has uprooted one stump as a souvenir. What a champion bowler! 8 wickets in the match for him and he stood tall whenever his skipper needed him. India go 1-0 up in the series.

OUT! BOWLED! Siraj comes up with a beautiful delivery. He dishes out a good length ball close to off and gets it to straighten just a hint to beat Anderson's attempt to block it from the back foot. It whistles past the outside edge and tickles the off stump behind. Start the celebration! India win by 151 runs!
Commentary.Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball, angling in from outside off. Anderson defends it from the crease.
PEACH! Full and just outside off. Anderson looks to block but gets beaten.
James Anderson is the last batsman.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jos Buttler runs out of patience and has a poke at a delivery. A touch short and outside off, Jos was leaving those well until now but this time goes to feel the ball. He is flat-footed inside the crease and gets a feather to the keeper. Rishabh Pant takes a simple catch and India get rid of the big fish.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: Starts with a length delivery on middle and leg, angling down, Buttler tries to flick but misses. It goes off his thigh pad to backward square leg.
Mohammed Siraj returns in the attack now.
Bumrah returns to over the wicket and angles in a length ball on off, Wood defends it to the off side.
Mark Wood arrives.

Big shout for an lbw!  The umpire stays still. It looks very close and Virat Kohli has wasted no time in taking the DRS. No inside edge and the ball is crashing onto the stumps. India get their breakthrough.

OUT! LBW! The resistance has finally been broken by Jasprit Bumrah and Ollie Robinson is in disbelief! The slower delivery from around the wicket is angled away a bit and Robinson misses his defensive shot. The ball goes on to hit Ollie on the back leg and the Indians appeal in unison. The umpire shakes his head but the review is taken quickly by Virat Kohli. We can see that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracker shows that the ball did pitch in line and it was going on to hit middle and off. The decision is overturned and the Indians can smell victory. Jos Buttler is still out there though.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Bumrah is peppering Robinson with the short ball now as he digs in another fierce one. Robinson manages to duck under this one as well and a no ball is called for overstepping.
Bumrah bowls a quick, short one on middle from around the stumps. Robinson once again does well to duck under it.
Full and straight. Robinson defends it well.
Full, around off. Robinson leans forward and pushes it onto the off side.
Quick bouncer, on middle, ends up way behind leg. Robinson ducks underneath and Pant makes a good stop diving to his left.
Length ball, on off. Buttler blocks it out. 10 overs remaining now.
Overpitched on middle. Buttler blocks it dead straight and past the bowler for a couple as Shami chases it down from mid on.
Pitched up, wide outside off. Buttler leaves it alone.
This one is angled in on middle and leg, looking for the lbw or the leading edge. Buttler manages to defend it.
On a good length, on off and again a bit of extra bounce. Buttler defends it off the higher part of the bat onto the off side.
Length ball, on the pads. Robinson works it to deep square leg for one.
Mohammed Siraj is back on for possibly his final burst in this Test match. Hang on a minute, Ishant Sharma will continue as Siraj was off the field and is not allowed to bowl currently.
Back of a length, a fair bit outside off. Jos Buttler shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Buttler makes the leave and the ball almost rolls along the ground towards the keeper.
Full, outside off but slower in pace. It was the double bluff but Buttler stays solid in defense.
More attacking field now. Short mid off, short mid on, short mid-wicket in place.
Angled in on middle and leg, Buttler dabs it down to silly mid on.
This one bounces a bit extra after pitching on a length around off. Buttler defends it from the higher portion of his bat.
Quick bumper, on off. Buttler ducks under it.
Length again, on the stumps but this one keeps low. Ollie Robinson does well to get his bat down in time.
Length ball, around off and shaping in. Robinson blocks it out.
Pitched up, on off. Jos Buttler pushes it through covers for three runs.
Length ball, outside off. Buttler leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball, on middle and leg, Buttler defends it down from the back foot.
Fractionally short in length and outside off, Jos allows it through by dropping his hands.
Shortish and on off, Robinson stays back and taps it down to point. Wants a run but Buttler sends him back.
A yorker outside off, Buttler squeezes it out through point for a single.
Bouncer, outside off, Buttler drops his wrists and allows it through.
Bumrah goes good length and arrows it around off, Buttler is on the front foot, not entirely, as he defends it to covers. A silly mid off has come in for any uppish drive.
Back of a length, just outside off, Buttler is not interested in playing at that.
Bumrah serves a good length ball on off, Buttler sticks on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller in length and on off, targeting the pads, Ollie has his bat down as he blocks. 84 balls left.
On a good length and close to off, holding its line, Ollie shoulders arms.
Fullish and outside off, Robinson drives but finds the cover fielder.
Ishant gets close to off but not close enough. It straightens with the extra bounce as Robinson pushes at it and misses.
A gentle good length delivery, again outside off, Ollie Robinson lets it be.
Back of a length, outside off, Robinson shoulders arms.

Time for one last mandatory break, a Drinks break. This contest has now reached boiling point and everyone can see that emotions are flying all over the ground. Mohammed Siraj got two-in-two a few overs ago and since then Buttler and Robinson have weathered the storm, somehow. Also, the final hour begins and 15 mandatory overs have to be bowled. We are all set for a thrilling finish! Ishant Sharma has been handed the ball.

EDGY FOUR! Identical to the last delivery, close to off and straightening a bit, Buttler tries to defend but it takes the outside edge and screams through the gap between slips and gully for a boundary.

Edged but safe. Bumrah hits the right area, around off on a length and gets it to straighten, Buttler brings a straight bat to keep it out but edges it behind. It falls short of KL Rahul at second slip.
Digs in a short ball but it's down the leg side, Buttler leaves and Pant dives across to his left to collect the ball.
Fuller in length and on off, angling in, Buttler defends it down safely.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Shortish and outside off, Buttler shoulders arms.

Jasprit Bumrah is brought back into the attack in an attempt to clean up the tail. Also, between overs, there was some more banter between Kohli and Robinson. Jos Buttler intervened and had a word with the Indian skipper.
Drifting down the leg side, fuller in length, Robinson tries to flick but misses. Another over ticks by. 16 left, one for the last hour to begin.
Shortish and on off, defended off the back foot to the off side.
Good skiddy pace from Shami, delivers it on a length and outside off, Ollie Robinson shoulders arms.
Back of a length, angling down the leg side, Robinson tries to flick but misses.
Fractionally short on middle, Robinson stays on the back foot, uses his wrists and works it to square leg.
Short in length and outside off, Ollie Robinson rocks back to cut but misses.
Slants in a full ball on off, staying down, Buttler does well to defend it back.
On a length and outside off, Buttler opens the face and steers it down to third man for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Siraj is on the pads, on a length and angling down, Buttler flicks it aerially but wide of leg gully for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, Buttler shoulders arms.
Siraj follows up the short ball with a fuller length, Robinson eases it down to long on for three runs.
Bouncer around middle, Ollie Robinson ducks underneath it.
Goes probing around off, fuller in length, Buttler defends it back to the bowler.
Beauty! Angling in around off and holding its line, Buttler tries his best to middle his defensive shot but it beats the outside edge.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Good length again, around off and holding its line, Buttler looks to play at it initially but then withdraws his bat.
Outside off, on a good length, Buttler allows it through.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it down.
Mohammed Shami is back into the attack. He has figures of 8-3-13-1 so far.

Drifting down the leg side, Ollie Robinson tries to flick and possibly gets a faint edge. Pant dives across to his left, Jadeja dives across to his right from leg gully but the ball drops in front and sneaks between them. They take a couple of runs.
Turns it off his pads to mid-wicket and takes a single. Ollie returns on strike and Kohli is heard saying to him, 'at 122 clicks, don't even think of playing outside England'. Hmmm...some banter!
A wayward bouncer, down the leg side, Buttler leaves and Pant flies to collect the ball. It comes out of his gloves as he lands but no run taken. Called a wide.
Slightly short and close to off, Robinson taps it down to cover-point and crosses for a brisk run. The point fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Siraj gets his line right and serves a full ball on off, Ollie defends it from the bottom part of his bat.
Another delivery down the leg side, once again Robinson tries to flick but misses. Pant collects and thinks about appealing. Only thinks, doesn't appeal.
Good length ball on leg, angling down, Ollie Robinson tries to flick but misses. Rishabh Pant does well to collect it by going down on his knees.
Loopy and full on off, Buttler is on the front foot as he defends it solidly.
Flatter and full on middle, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fires one down the leg side, Buttler pads it away again and the short fine leg fielder makes the stop.
Quicker one, fired down the leg side, Jos padded it away.
A touch short and flat on off, Ollie goes on the back foot and punches it to covers where the fielder fumbles and allows a run.
Floated ball, full and on middle, Ollie Robinson defends it off the front foot.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works it through square leg for a single. India won't mind Ollie on strike.
Angling down the leg side, on middle and leg, Ollie tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to fine leg and they take a couple of leg byes.

Goodness me, what a delivery! This one shoots off from the surface, after landing on a shortish length around middle, Robinson tries to defend but misses and takes a blow on his chest. Unplayable. Siraj gives a stare.
No hat-trick. Back of a length, outside off, Robinson stays back and shoulders arms.
Ollie Robinson walks out to face the hat trick ball!

OUT! Sam Curran bags a King Pair! India are rampant, they are on a roll. Beauty from Mohammed Siraj again. He lands it in the line of the stumps and gets it to move away from the batsman. Curran has not stretched out enough in his stance as he tries to defend. But the ball takes the outside edge and settles into the gloves of Rishabh Pant. A mirror image almost of Moeen's dismissal. India can smell victory now. This is the first-ever King Pair at Lord's, poor Sam. Mohammed Siraj is on a hat-trick...
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: Who will come in to bat next? Sam Curran is the new man in.

OUT! Here is the breakthrough India were waiting for! Siraj beat the outside edge on multiple occasions in the last over and this time the ball has kissed the outside edge. Outstanding bowling from Siraj. He has hardly gone wicket-less in his spells. Serves it close to middle and off and takes it away from the left-hander, Moeen tries to defend without moving his feet and edges it behind. Virat Kohli, at first slip, makes no mistake as he completes the catch to his right. 21.5 overs left to negotiate for England, India need 4 wickets.
Commentary.Howout: c Virat Kohli b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary.Commentary: Quicker one, full and on middle, Buttler flicks but finds square leg.
Edgy! Jadeja comes from 'round the wicket and bowls a flighted full ball on off, Buttler leans forward to defend but it takes the outside edge. The ball rolls towards second slip.
Very full and on off, Buttler is forward as he defends it watchfully to the off side.
Slower again, full and around leg, Jos defends it from the front foot.
Slower through the air, full and landing outside leg, Buttler pads it away.
Fuller and flatter on middle, defended back.
Around off, seaming away, once again Moeen tries to push at it tamely and misses.
Full and on off, Moeen is very compact in his defense this time as he keeps it out to the off side.
Almost edges it behind. Some great lines from Siraj. Delivers it on a length around middle and gets it to nip away, Moeen hangs his bat down in defense but it beats the outside edge by a whisker.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
Shaping away from the batsman, on a length, Moeen pokes at it but misses.
Back of a length, around middle and off, defended off the back foot.
This time Jadeja angles it away from around the stumps. Buttler leaves the ball which is outside the off stump.
Fuller delivery, around off. Buttler puts out a stride to defend.
On off, slightly shorter. Buttler defends it off the front foot.
Fuller ball, on the stumps. Ali pushes it to the leg side for a single.
Jadeja fires one in from around off. Ali looks to sweep but pulls out of the shot.
Loopy ball, on off. Ali defends it well.

SHOUT FOR A CAUGHT BEHIND! Jadeja begins with a flatter delivery outside off, gets it to break back in, Moeen is on the back foot as he tries to defend. Misses completely but there is some noise as it goes into the gloves of Pant. The Indians appeal but to no avail. Virat Kohli has a word with his keeper, Ishant, who was at point, says that he heard a noise. The Indian skipper takes the DRS but before anything can happen, the third umpire intervenes and informs that 'no point' as it's a no ball for overstepping. That's a first for me. Hang on, the Ultra Edge detects a spike, so Moeen is very lucky here.
Ravindra Jadeja is back into the attack now. 3-2-2-0 are his figures so far.
Bowls it from wide of the crease and delivers a full ball on middle, Buttler leans across a bit more in his stance as he pushes it down to mid on.
Pitches it up and outside off, inviting the drive, Buttler turns down the proposal as he makes a leave.
Shout for a caught behind! But it dies down immediately. That appeal was more in hope than expectation. A length ball close to off, holding its line, Buttler feels inside the line and misses.
Siraj gets closer to the line of the stumps, fuller in length, Buttler keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it to mid on.
Good length delivery, wide outside off, Buttler has nothing to do with it.
Fullish and on off, slanting in, Buttler is on the front foot with a dead bat as he blocks.

Time for a Drinks break. India started from where they left off after Tea and got Joe Root out in the first over after the break. Since then, the Indian bowlers have probed and probed but Jos Buttler and Moeen Ali have held their own. Apart from the dropped catch of Buttler by the Indian skipper, the English batsmen haven't given away many chances. It is poised nicely at the moment, with everyone on the edge of their seats. 26 overs, 5 wickets - that's the equation.
Too straight in line from Shami, Moeen closes the face of his bat and gently works it past short leg for a couple of runs.
A length ball on middle and leg, Jos tucks it through square leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Buttler defends it with an angled bat to the off side.

Oohhh...that was perilously close to the off stick. Shami lands it on a length around off, going up the slope from the Nursery End, Buttler is in two minds, whether to play or leave and gets beaten as the ball whistles past the bat.
On middle, a fuller length ball, Moeen works it behind square leg for a run.
EDGED BUT SAFE! Shami angles in a length ball on top of off, Moeen stays back to defend but edges it behind. It drops in front of Rohit Sharma at second slip.
Siraj intentionally bowls it full and wide outside off, asking Buttler to go for another drive, the batter obliges but mistimes his shot off the toe end. It rolls back to the bowler.
FOUR! Thumped! Slightly overpitched from Siraj, around off, Buttler presses forward and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary. He is in a defensive mode but still puts away the bad ball.
In the channel outside off, once again Jos is content in leaving deliveries outside off.
Shortish and outside off, curling back in off the seam, Buttler covers his stumps and shoulders arms. Big movement on this one.
Beats the outside edge. Siraj bowls it on a good length again, outside off and shaping in, Buttler tries to feel the ball and gets beaten.
Siraj begins his new spell with a good length delivery outside off, Buttler offers no shot. Rishabh Pant collects it on one bounce.
Mohammed Siraj comes in to replace Jasprit Bumrah. 4-1-13-0 are his figures so far.
Around off on a good length, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, left alone.

Almost drags it on! FOUR! Shami puts it on a fuller length around off, shaping in, Moeen decides to leave it but it's a late call. The ball takes the inner edge, beats the stumps and rushes past leg gully for a boundary at fine leg. It's good for Ali that he didn't succeed in his decision to leave because that ball was heading for the stumps.
Bouncer around off, Moeen ducks with ease.
Once again Shami is right on the money, angles in a length ball on off, Moeen is also very alert as he defends it to the off side.
Shami bowls it on a length and close to off, from 'round the wicket, Moeen defends it in the direction of mid on.
Full and swinging in, from around off, Buttler defends it back to the bowler. Another over played out, that's what England would be thinking at the moment. 29 more to go.
Darts in a good length from around off, Buttler meets it with a dead bat in defense.
Outside off, left alone.
A similar delivery but the line was quite wide outside off, an easy leave for Jos Buttler.
Fullish and arrowing in from outside off, Buttler defends it from the bottom half of his bat.
Axar Patel is on the field for Ishant Sharma.
Bumrah is bowling from over the wicket now to Moeen. Delivers it very full on middle, Ali pushes it gently to extra cover for a single.
This one moves into the batsman, from a length around off, Buttler has his eyes glued to the ball as he blocks it down to the pitch.
On a driving length this time, Buttler stretches his front leg forward to cover the line and shoulders arms. Much better!
Ufff, that was so close! Shami dishes out an outswinger around off, on a length, he draws the false shot from Buttler, who pushes inside the line and misses.
Slightly fuller than the last one, around off, Jos defends it back.
Good length ball close to off, seaming away, Buttler defends it from the crease.
Starts his spell with a short delivery outside off, shaping away, Jos shoulders arms.
Mohammed Shami is back into the attack. So far, he has figures of, 5-2-5-1!
That is defended solidly by Moeen to complete the over. 31 overs left in the day's play.
Excellent delivery, a bit fuller around off, there is a bit of late away movement as well, Moeen tries to defend but takes his bat near his body to let it go.
Bumrah keeps targeting the stumps, on a good length, Moeen is very solid in his defense.
Spears it in, full and on middle, Moeen has his bat down in time as he blocks it towards the bowler.
Arrows in a full length ball on off, Moeen defends it from the crease. The umpire has a look at the bowler's followthrough.
Good judgement show by Ali. It's a length ball around off, straightening a bit, Moeen trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms.
Ishant bends his back and lets out a short ball around off, Jos ducks.
Fuller and closer to off, this time the ball is holding its line, Buttler pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Full inswinging delivery on off, Buttler has his bat down in time as he defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length and wide outside off, Buttler shoulders arms.
A stifled appeal for an lbw! Fuller in length around middle and leg, angling down, Jos fails to flick and takes a blow on his pads. Missing leg.
Fuller in length and on middle, Buttler flicks it to mid-wicket where the fielder makes a half-stop and parries it to mid on.
Angling in from around off, on a good length, Moeen shows the full face of his bat as he keeps it out safely.
A touch short and on off, Moeen has just blocked that from his crease.
A length ball on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.

DROPPED! Kohli puts it down. Bumrah delivers it short and wide outside off, Buttler throws his bat at it and gets a big fat outside edge. The ball flies to first slip where Virat Kohli tries to catch it with his fingers pointing up but it bursts through and goes behind. The batsmen switch ends.
Angling in from a length around off, Jos stays on the back foot and defends it to covers.
Play and a miss! Another quality delivery. Back of a length, outside off and skidding on, Buttler tries defending but misses.

EDGED BUT SAFE! After bowling a few to come in, Ishant gets one full length ball to straighten from around off, Buttler hangs his bat out in defense but it takes the outside edge and drops in front of the two slip fielder. It sneaks past them after that and the batters take a run.
Ishant keeps his length full and delivers it close to off, Buttler brings his bat down and pushes it down to mid on.
Some swing in the air, full and around off, Buttler presents a straight bat as he blocks it to the off side.
Angling down the leg side, fuller in length, Buttler tries to flick but misses. Pant collects and appeals but nothing from the umpire. There was some noise but it didn't sound woody.
Hurls a length ball in the channel outside off, shaping away a bit, Buttler offers no shot.
Full in length and around off, Buttler brings down a straight bat and defends it back.
Beaten! Back of a length, close to off and shaping away, Moeen stays back to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Moeen is off the mark as well. Bumrah delivers a length ball on the pads and Ali has no issues in flicking it fine down the leg side. Jadeja tries his best in the deep but fails to pull it back. A boundary results.
Effort delivery, a bumper on middle, Moeen ducks and Pant leaps to collect it.
Good length ball on off, angling in, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller in length and on middle, Buttler clips it behind square leg and takes a single to open his account.
A length ball outside off, staying low, Buttler defends it back from the back foot.
Rohit Sharma is standing a few steps ahead at second slip. He is also wearing his helmet.
In the channel outside off, Moeen makes another leave to complete the over.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Ishant gets closer to off, Moeen tries to defend but keeps his bat close to the body. The ball straightens and whizzes past the edge.
Quite wide outside off, shaping away, Moeen allows it through.
Angles it in around off and takes it away off the seam, Moeen is on the back foot to defend but is beaten.
Full in length and angling down the leg side, Jos tries to flick but misses. It clips his pads and goes behind. Pant dives across to his left and parries it to fine leg for a leg bye.
Ishant Sharma to steam in from the other end.
On a length and close to off, cutting back in, Moeen keeps it out off the inner half to square leg.
Bumrah moves to 'round the wicket angle, serves it on a length and close to off, Moeen offers no shot.
A bouncer around leg, Moeen ducks at the last moment.
Moeen Ali walks out to bat in a pressure situation.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! A huge blow to England, their skipper is dismissed in the first over after Tea. Root is looking down in disappointment. Is this the final nail in the coffin? Bumrah delivers for his team yet again. Hurls across a good length delivery outside off from wide of the crease, holding its line, Root is on the back foot and has a gentle poke inside the line. It takes the outside edge and goes to Virat Kohli at first slip. The Indian skipper is alert and takes the catch safely. The Indian players know the value of this wicket and the celebration from them is once again massive. Root had edged quite a few deliveries in the first innings as well but then they were landing short of the slip fielders. Not this time.
Commentary.Howout: c Virat Kohli b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Good length ball on off, shaping in, Root defends it off the back foot.
Fuller in length and outside off, on a driving length to tempt the batsman, Root is not chaing it.

We're back, folks! After four days of exciting Test cricket, we are down to the last session. Only two results are possible now and India would be gunning for a win. 6 wickets more for a series lead. Can Joe Root guide his team to safety? Let's find out. Jos Buttler has joined his skipper and it will be interesting to find his approach. It's all about survival now. Jasprit Bumrah to kick off proceedings. All the lights are on at the moment. Here we go...
... DAY 5, FINAL SESSION ...

With Jonny Bairstow removed at the stroke of Tea, England are in a big spot of bother. They have 38 overs to negotiate with 6 wickets left in the kitty. Needless to say, Joe Root will be the key and they won't mind some help from the heavens. There was a mild drizzle and light could become an issue as the evening progresses. Do join us at 3 pm GMT (4 pm local) for all the action from the last session of the Lord's Test.

What a lively finish to the afternoon session, a fitting end! India declared after batting for just 9 balls and then came out all guns blazing with the ball. Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Shami combined to send the English openers back to the pavilion in no time. After that, it was a display of some extraordinary seam bowling. Haseeb Hameed got an early life in his innings and batted for around an hour with his skipper Joe Root in an 83-ball stand.

OUT! LBW! Lightning has struck on the last ball before Tea. Ishant Sharma and India are elated as the decision is overturned. Length ball, around off and nipping back in sharply. Bairstow looks to block but the ball goes through the gate and raps him on the back pad. There is a huge appeal from the Indians but the umpire shakes his head. Height could be an issue here. Virat Kohli does take the review at the last moment after having a word with his boys. Ultra Edge shows no involvement of the bat and Ball Tracker then shows three reds. A huge roar can be heard from the Indian crowd as this one was crashing into the middle stump. Kohli is screaming in joy. Joe Root is one more partner short as Jonny Bairstow has to depart as well.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ishant Sharma

Commentary.Commentary: DRS time! Huge shout for an lbw against Jonny Bairstow. Not given. Looks too high. Virat Kohli takes the DRS after consulting his players. No bat involved and the Ball Tracker shows that it's crashing into the stumps. What a review!
Shorter in length and just outside off. Bairstow bends his back to move away from that one.
Pitched up around off and straightening off the seam. Bairstow watchfully keeps it out.
Pitched up, around middle. Bairstow nudges it towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Root goes back into his crease and guides it to third man for a single.
Fuller in length and outside off, on a driving length to tempt the batter, Root is not chasing it.
Pitched up, around middle and straightening off the seam. Bairstow gets behind the line to defend it.
Full, on leg stump and further going down. Bairstow looks to tickle it fine but maybe it took the pad on the way to the keeper.
Length ball, shaping away from off stump. Bairstow makes a good leave.
Very full, on off. Bairstow does well to keep that one out.
Beaten! Full in length and just outside off, Bairstow tries to defend close to his body but it nips away a shade to beat the outside edge.
A leg cutter, around off, Root taps it down to cover-point and pinches a single.

FIVE RUNS! Shami strays down leg again and once again the ball just swings miles after going past the batsman. Root leaves it alone and Pant dives a long way but still gets beaten as the ball races into the fence. No ball for overstepping has been called as well. So everything was wrong with this delivery.
Mohammed Shami is back into the attack minutes before Tea. 1/3 in his 4 overs so far. There's a leg gully in place.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Bairstow nudges it towards mid on.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping away this time. Bairstow shoulders arms.
Good length delivery, on off and angling in. Bairstow stays watchful in defense.
Length ball, swinging in, on the pads, Root easily flicks it to deep square leg and collects a run.
Short in length, just outside off and keeping low. Root looks to cut close to his body but misses. That wasn't too far away from the outside edge.
Back of a length, around off and shaping in. Root taps it off the back foot to point.
Shortish and on off, Root goes back and taps it down with gentle hands to covers for a single.
Identical to the last delivery, Root flicks across the line but finds the fielder at square leg.
On middle and leg, Jonny works it through square leg and rotates the strike.
Gentle loosener, going down leg. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Full, on off. Root clears his front leg and flicks it through square leg for one.
Siraj pitches this one fuller, around off. Root presents a dead bat at it in defense.
Full and straight, Root flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Back of a length, coming in around the hips. Bairstow flicks it off the back foot towards fine leg for one.
This one swings back in from a length outside off. Bairstow watchfully keeps it out.
On a good length and on the stumps. Bairstow nudges it to silly mid on.
Length ball, on off. Bairstow defends it well.

A touch fuller and in the line of the stumps, this one lands and straightens as Root shapes up to flick it on the leg side. Closes the face of the bat early and the leading edge takes it towards point. It's in the gap and they take a run.
Full and straight. Bairstow pushes it to silly mid on which had come in place just before this delivery.
An action replay of the previous delivery except that this one shapes away even more. Easy leave for Bairstow.
On a good length, outside off and swinging away. Bairstow makes a tentative leave.
Fuller, on off. Root drives it through covers for one.

FOUR! Half a chance for Rishabh Pant! Length ball, swinging in from middle and leg. Root looks to glance and gets it very fine, off a thin inside edge. Pant dives across to his left and just about gets a hand to it as the ball races away to the fence.
Full and swinging in. Root flicks it straight to backward square leg.
Back of a length, around off. Bairstow stays solid in defense.
Length ball, on the stumps. Bairstow blocks it out.

FOUR LEG BYES! Extra bounce and vicious movement. Ishan digs it in short around off, Jonny Bairstow is taken by surprise as he tries to duck. It brushes something, maybe the shoulder or the helmet of the batsman, before looping behind the keeper for a boundary.
Jonny Bairstow is the new batsman.

The finger has gone up after the lbw appeal against Haseeb Hameed. He takes the DRS immediately. Has he edged it? Nopes. No bat involved. The Ball Tracker shows that it's clipping the top of the leg stump. Umpire's call.

OUT! LBW! That ball came back in sharply! Ishant Sharma has made an immediate impact for India as he breaks a very important partnership. Haseeb Hameed did all the hard work but just could not do anything about this one. The ball pitches on a good length around off and nips back in venomously. Hameed looks to block but the ball goes through the gate and raps him on the pads. Huge appeal and the finger is raised. Haseeb Hameed takes the review straightaway, maybe he thought that he got some bat. The replays roll in, nothing on the Ultra Edge and the Ball Tracker shows that it's clipping the top of the leg stump. Umpire's call and England lose their third wicket.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ishant Sharma

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Root stays back and runs it down to third man for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Root leaves it alone as the ball keeps low on its way to the keeper. That one scuttled through to Pant, almost on two bounces.
Bowling change. Ishant Sharma is now inserted into the attack.
Siraj mixes his length this time and digs in a short ball around off, an easy leave for Haseeb who ducks.
Fuller this time, around off and angling in, Hameed defends it near his front pad. Very watchful of Siraj and the slope.
Delivers it on a length outside off, shaping in, Hameed again leaves it. Pant collects it on one bounce.
An inswinger, on a length outside off, Haseeb shoulders arms.
Siraj is maintaining a good line, bowling it in the line of the stumps, Hameed is content in blocking from the crease.
Dishes out a full length ball on off, Hameed gets on the front foot and defends it right under his watchful eyes.
Floated and full on middle, Root taps it on the leg side, finds mid-wicket.
Bowls it in the flatter trajectory, short and outside off, Root cuts it from the back foot to short point. That silly point fielder had moved a few yards back.
Tossed up ball on middle, fuller in length, Joe flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Floated and full on off, Joe defends it through the line to covers.
Shortish, flat and on off, Root defends it from the back foot.
Loopy and full on off, Root lunges and pushes it to point. Sets off for a run but then aborts.
Siraj goes very full this time, around off, Hameed digs it out down to mid on.
Wrong line, a length ball on middle and on leg, Hameed tickles it down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
On a length, around middle and leg, Root eases it behind square leg and picks up a single.
Fullish and on off, angling in, Root drives it down the ground and the mid on fielder makes the stop to his left.
A length ball on off, shaping in, Root decides to defend but it takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket.
Siraj begins with a delivery around off, fuller in length, Root wrists it through square leg and picks up a couple of runs.
Bowling change. Mohammed Siraj into the attack for the first time today. He picked a 4-wicket haul in the first innings and by far was the best Indian pacer.
Slower through the air, full and around leg, Root tucks it off his pads to deep square leg and retains strike with a single.
A touch short and flat on off, Joe is on the back foot as he blocks.
Too full in length and outside off, Root gets forward and drives but finds the cover fielder.
Fuller and on middle, Hameed uses his wrists and works it behind square leg for a single.
Floated and around off, going straight on, Hameed covers his stumps and leaves.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to mid on.
Pitches it up and outside off, shaping in, Root judges the line well and shoulders arms.
Bumrah bowls a fuller length ball just outside off, shaping in, Root has things under control after striding his front foot forward as he allows it through to the keeper.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, Joe has nothing to offer.
Quite wide outside off, inviting the batsman to chase, Root is in no mood to do that and lets it be.
FOUR! Easy pickings for a batsman in form. Fuller length ball on middle and leg, angling down at 88 mph, Root tickles it neatly down to fine leg for a boundary.
Angles in a length ball on off, targeting the off stump, Root defends it solidly off his front foot.
Fires it flat and short on middle, arm ball, Hameed pushes himself on the back foot and blocks it down. Jadeja's over goes by in a flash.
Loopy and full outside off, Hameed gets on the front foot and defends it to covers.
Floated and full on off, staying low, Hameed is on the back foot again as he pushes it back to the bowler off the leading edge.
Quicker and flatter, an arm ball, Hameed goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Tossed up ball outside off, Haseeb Hameed covers his stumps and lets it through.
Full and flighted, landing on off, Haseeb is forward as he blocks.
Bowling change. Ravindra Jadeja has been brought into the attack.
FOUR! Root plays his pet shot to fine the fence. Back of a length and outside off, Root hangs on the back foot, opens the face of his bat late and guides it down to third man for a boundary.
Bumrah delivers it full and close to off, Root is forward as he pushes it to extra cover.
Good length delivery outside off, holding its line, Root allows it through again.
Bumrah pitches it full and outside off, Root takes his front leg forward and then leaves.
Mohammed Shami has gone off the field for a breather.
Back of a length, outside off, Root shoulders arms.

FOUR BYES! Fine leg is turning out to be very productive for England. Bumrah tries to spear in a full ball but it's on middle and leg and swings down the leg side. Beats the bat of Root and Pant to find the fence. This ball is hooping around at the moment.
A gentle delivery, on a length and outside off, Haseeb Hameed leaves it. Pant collects it on one bounce.
Another delivery outside off, Haseeb shoulders arms. So Shami is controlling his outswingers well but is struggling to put his inswingers.
An outswinger outside off, left alone.
FOUR BYES! Shami has done it again. Fails to control his line and delivers it well down the leg side. No chance for the batter or keeper as the ball scoots away to the fine leg fence.

Beaten comprehensively. A length ball close to off, nipping away, Haseeb tries to defend but it moves away to beat the edge. At the moment, there is art at one end and struggle at other, quips Harsha Bhogle (on air).
FOUR BYES! Wayward line from Shami. He sprays a shortish delivery way down the leg side, Hameed allows it through and Pant fails to reach it even with a full-length dive. A boundary at fine leg.
Bumrah fires in another fuller length ball on off, Root pushes it back to the bowler to end the over.
Too full in length and outside off, Root opens the face of his bat as he presses forward and crunches his drive to point. Finds Jadeja.
A length delivery in the zone outside off, once again Root covers his stumps with a positive stride and then makes a leave.
A bit of drizzle now.
On a length and outside off, Root strides to cover the stumps and shoulders arms.
What a reply from Bumrah! Delivers it on a length and close to off, shaping away late, Root is forward to defend but it whizzes past the outside edge. Pant dives to his right to collect the ball.
FOUR! Shot! Root will play his shots. Short in length and outside off, Root is on top of the bounce as he goes for the pull and just rolls his wrists to play it through square leg for a boundary.
Identical to the last delivery, Haseeb Hameed gets on the front foot and defends it solidly near his front pad.
Slants in a length ball on off, straightening a bit, Hameed hangs back to defend but it takes the outer half and rolls in front of gully.
In the channel outside off, the batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Down the leg side, Hameed allows it through and Pant collects with a dive to his left.

EDGED BUT DROPPED! Rohit has failed to grab it. Back of a length, around off, Hameed pushes inside the line and edges it to second slip. Rohit Sharma stretches to his left, trying to cup it with both hands, but it hits his wrists and runs behind. The batsmen take two.
Slightly overpitched and outside off, Hameed drives it through the line but finds the cover fielder.
Hurls across a length delivery in the channel outside off, Root guards his stumps and makes a leave.
Back of a length, around off, Root is on the back foot again as he pushes it defensively to covers.
Around off on a good length, angling in and staying down, Joe is on the back foot as he defends it down on the pitch.

FOUR! Shot of a batsman in prime form! Bumrah pitches it up and around off, Root leans into the drive and caresses it through cover-point for a boundary. Opens his account in style and the crowd goes Roooootttt.
Good length delivery again, this time on off, Root stays on the back foot and defends it down.
Good length ball outside off, angling in, Root plays late at it and pushes it towards point. Lets out a loud scream of no.
Shaping away from the batsman outside off, Hameed shoulders arms to survive the over.
Back of a length, in the region outside off, Hameed stays back and lets it be.
Peach of a delivery! Shami is on fire. Gets close to off, on a length and around off, Haseeb has to play at it but the away movement beats the outside edge.
Slightly short this time, outside off and moving away off the seam, if it's not in the line of the stumps, it's easy for Haseeb Hameed to deal. He leaves it alone.
Angling in and taking it out. That's the plan from Shami. On a good length just outside off, Haseeb shoulders arms as it shapes away.
A bouncer from Shami, around off, Hameed lets it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up and outside off, shaping in, Root is forward as he defends it to the off side.
Angling into the batsman, on a length around off, Hameed flicks it softly past the diving short mid-wicket fielder. The batsmen get three runs and the crowd is cheering every run here.
On a driving length outside off, skidding off the surface, Hameed presses forward before making a leave.
Bouncer around middle and leg, at 80 mph, Hameed ducks.
Shortish and on off, Hameed is on his toes as he defends it down.
Good length ball on middle, defended from the crease to mid-wicket.

Hameed is off the mark in this Test match and the crowd roars. On a good length and around off, shaping away, Hameed pushes at it tamely and gets an outside edge. It drops in front of the second slip fielder and he deflects it towards the left side of the keeper. Root spots the chance and calls Haseeb through for a single.
Short in length and around off, Root sways away from the line of fire. The keeper fumbles and the batters cross.
Joe Root, the skipper, comes out to bat with his team in a spot of bother.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! That's a pearler from Mohammed Shami. This one is more closer to off and it's an outswinger. Unplayable to be honest. Dominic Sibley is on the back foot as he tries to defend the line. But the ball nips away slightly to take a thin outside edge. Rishabh Pant catches it, Shami is running in celebration, the Indian players are appealing but the finger stays down. Hang on, Dominic Sibley is seen walking. It's all happening at Lord's. The Indian players are over the moon. Both the English openers are back in the shed without troubling the scorers.
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Shami

Commentary.Commentary: Shami gets closer to the off stump line with a length ball, Sibley presses forward to cover the line and shoulders arms.
A bit short in length and on off, Sibley taps it down wide of gully and comes out in search of a run. Haseeb Hameed sends him back. A good call.
Shami begins with an outswinger! It lands on a good length outside off, Sibley doesn't offer any shot.
Who will be Bumrah's bowling partner from the other end? An upbeat Mohammed Shami it is!
Bumrah bangs in a short delivery, outside off, Hameed drops his wrists, takes his eyes away and allows it to go. Excellent first over by Jasprit Bumrah.
This one is on a good length and outside off, Hameed is nicely forward to cover his stumps as he makes a leave.
Short-leg to be put in place now.
Spicy delivery! A touch short in length and outside off, zipping in with extra bounce. Hameed pushes inside the line and misses. Haseeb survives a king pair.
Who will come in at number 3? Haseeb Hameed walks out in the middle. He bagged a golden duck in the first innings.

OUT! BURNS IS GONE! The Indian players are celebrating big. Perfect start for them. Bumrah hurls across a delivery around leg at 87 mph, a touch short and Burns tries to work it on the leg side but the ball moves a bit to take the leading edge. Mohammed Siraj takes an easy catch running across at covers. The crowd erupts. Rory can't believe it. He has played at a delivery outside the line of the leg stump and got a leading edge, Dominic Sibley can tell him a bit about this kind of dismissal.
Commentary.Howout: c Mohammed Siraj b Jasprit Bumrah

Commentary.Commentary: Shortish and on middle, shaping away, Burns is squared up and defends it off the outer half to point.
Good length ball close to off, angling away, Burns covers his stumps and shoulders arms. Called a no ball for overstepping. Jasprit Bumrah bowled a few in the first innings too.
Right on the money. Bumrah delivers it on a back of a length, around middle, some extra bounce as well, Burns tries to defend but it jumps up and hits him on the gloves.
